  "confidence": 0.95,
  "reasoning": "The Acer TravelMate 5735Z laptop has broken ACPI video backlight control and needs native backlight instead. The fix requires adding a DMI quirk entry in the video_detect_dmi_table array in drivers/acpi/video_detect.c to call video_detect_force_native for this specific laptop model (matching DMI_SYS_VENDOR='Acer', DMI_PRODUCT_NAME='TravelMate 5735Z', DMI_BOARD_NAME='BA51_MV'). This quirk was later added upstream (commit reference: https://bugzilla.kernel.org/show_bug.cgi?id=207835) but is missing in Linux 5.6.7. Without this quirk, the kernel incorrectly uses ACPI video backlight control which doesn't work on this hardware, while the native intel_backlight interface works correctly."
}

